1.title: Earth, Fire and Water
1.plot: Neil Perry, Ben Shewry and Peter Gilmore meet in Hobart, Tasmania to start piecing together their world-class menu. Inspired by the picturesque surrounds of the River Derwent, they agree on a theme for the first course; fire-roasted Australian seafood. The chefs then head their separate ways, tracing their chosen ingredients to passionate producers scattered across the country.

2.title: Art and Produce
2.plot: Determined to amaze guests when seated at the iconic Museum of Old and New Art, Neil, Ben and Peter decide on their main dishes before heading out across the country in search of ingredients. Neil visits Victoria's High Country to talk to David Blackmore about his pure-blood Wagyu beef, Ben ventures into the great Australian outback to learn about Red Kangaroos and Peter travels to the east coast of Tasmania in search of abalone.

3.title: An Experience to Remember
3.plot: As the day of the event dawns, the chefs carefully prepare their dishes for 250 international guests as the picturesque locations are being set up. The 250 international guests luxuriate in each dish, appreciating their foray into the best of Australian cuisine.

Melbourne, Victoria, Australia::(Ben Shewry's Restaurant, Niel Perry's Restaurant)
Hobart, Tasmania, Australia::(MONA Museum, Lark Distillery)
Margaret River, Western Australia, Australia::(Cullen Wines)
Kimberly Coast, Western Australia, Australia::(Cygnet Bay Pearls)
Windsor, New South Wales, Australia::(Johnstone's Family Farm)
Bruny Island, Tasmania, Australia::(Bruny Island Cheese Company)
imdb.plot outline: Follow iconic chefs Neil Perry, Ben Shewry and Peter Gilmore on an indulgent culinary journey to Australia's finest farms, barns and cellar doors to source the best local ingredients for a world-class meal. Revelling in Australia's natural beauty and diversity, the chefs gather produce from across the country before transforming fresh ingredients into a series of delicious dishes in their award-winning kitchens. Culminating in the most ambitious culinary event of their careers, the chefs regroup at the infamous Museum of Old and New Art (MONA) in Tasmania to host a dinner for 250 of the world's toughest food critics.
imdb.title: Restaurant Australia
plot: follow renowned chefs Neil Perry, Ben Shewry and Peter Gilmore on a culinary journey across Australia as they source fresh local produce and create a menu set to impress some of the world's toughest critics.
